[S] Well now, I don't know. We don't have many elves in our ranks. They tend to side with the Empire.

[S] We're always glad to welcome another true son of Skyrim to our ranks.

[S] You really want to join our cause? Most of you foreigners don't seem to give a damn about Skyrim's oppression. | I guess being dragged to the headsman's block for no reason opened your eyes to the truth about the Empire, eh?
G|It's Jarl Ulfric you want. He'll decide if you're worthy to join our ranks.
G|Go on in. Jarl Ulfric likes to welcome all the new recruits personally.

Cell.Text: [S] Then you've come to the right place. The sons of Skyrim will never stop until... | Hold on, you were at Helgen, weren't you? One of the unlucky sods that were going to be executed along with us. | Look who it is, Galmar!

Node.Caption: MQ102UlfricIntroTopic: I'm here to join your fight against the Empire.

Cell.Text: How did you manage to escape Helgen?
Anyone who made it out of that nightmare must either be favored by the gods or damnably competent. | Either way, I'll be glad to have you on our side.

Node.Caption: MQ102UlfricIntroB1: It wasn't easy, but I survived.

Cell.Text: Yet here you are. I know as well as you do that many good people still support the Empire out of misguided loyalty.
Unfortunately, he hasn't made it back yet. I'm glad to hear he got out of Helgen at least. | I'm sure he'll make his way here eventually. Nothing but death would stop that one from doing his duty.
Ah, you must be the one Ralof was talking about! | Yes, he got here just fine, but he's already back out in the field.

Node.Caption: MQ102UlfricIntroB3: Ralof helped me escape. Has he made it back yet?

Cell.Text: [S] G|What do you think, Galmar? Can you use him?
Changed your mind? You ready to pledge your blood and honor for Skyrim's freedom?

Cell.Text: G|Then you're in the wrong place. We only want those who are committed to the cause. | Come back when you're sure, or go join the Legion. I hear they'll take anybody with a pulse.

Cell.Text: That's the spirit! Swear loyalty to our cause, and you'll be one of us. Repeat after me. | "I do swear my blood and honor to the service of Ulfric Stormcloak..."
